North Docks
I don't know what the boss was thinking
taking this request, we're engineers not
biologists, we make machines not living
creatures. There is no way we will make
this deadline.
Dec 5/23
The boss took a multi-billion contract to
bring woolly mamoths back to life without
thinking, and now us scientist need to
pickup the slack and fulfill his promises.
I swear, this will be my last job working
for Josephi Krakowski, after this, I quit!
Dec 8/23
Spent the last couple days looking into
previous attempts to revive the woolly
mamoth, turns out there has been hundreds
of attempts made already, but no one
has been able to get woolly mamoth DNA
let alone find a way to clone them.
It's done! We've finaly finished the
machine, searching for DNA cell by cell,
then simulating rapid growth through
electric pulses, all brought to life by a
neural network constantly improving the
model of the mamoths brain.
The machine is finished! and we have
a new pet woolly mamoth! now we just
need to hand it off in two days. but
tonight we rest, the entire teams feeling
under the weather after watching the
machine run for 2 days straight.
I've figured it out, instead of making the
mamoth ourselves why not make a machine
to figure it out for us! its genious! We can
make an analyser to pull apart fossils at
a celular level and look for any traces of
DNA.
Jermy says he has another Idea of what
we can do with the machine in the downtime
while we wait for the handoff. The rest
of us are still feeling sick so Jermy will be
working by himself, he says we will be
surprised by what he came up with.
